diff:1574460643:1574443676:=34c34%0a%3c !!%25center%25'''The Miami Infoshop'''%0a---%0a> !!%25center%25'''The Order of Saint Cervantes de Valladolid'''%0a38,39c38,39%0a%3c A collective of the bizarre people of Miami.  They are primarily concerned with their own protection, but work with the Executive Circle to stay in the know regarding what’s going on in Miami.  The Infoshop espouses anarchist and libertarian socialist values, and lets its members pursue their own interests free of oversight or interference.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> A secretive Catholic Order dedicated to contain and purge supernatural threats to their community.  The group also welcomes practitioners of Santeria and other Catholic-syncretic faiths.%0a> %0a41,42c41,42%0a%3c A framed and tattered black cloth hangs on the walls of the Infoshop, above the bike-repair area.  The flag - a relic of the Infoshop’s involvement in the Second National March on Washington for Lesbian and Gay Rights - barely survived the event.  It now stands as a memorial for those who the Infoshop fights for.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Order’s base in Miami, the Church of the Holy Mother, houses a reliquary common to all of the Order’s churches.  The reliquary, a simple hawthorn box tied with old leather, supposedly contains the ring finger of Saint Cervantes de Valladolid himself.  It is the Order’s faith in the Saint and his cause that propels them forward in their purpose.%0a> %0a44,45c44,45%0a%3c The doctrine of the Miami Infoshop is usually expressed in quick slogans:  "Eat the Rich," "Kill Your Heroes," and "Three Word Chant" being the most popular.  In reality, the group is loosely organized in a horizontal manner, where members choose their own level of involvement.  A good number of the Infoshop's mundane membership participates as the shop's librarians, bicycle repair team, and Food Not Bombs volunteers, but anybody is welcome to fulfill any role.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Within the Order, the number one goal is to understand and eliminate threats to the Catholic community they are a part of.  In Miami and their resulting membership in the Executive Circle, they have expanded their mission to the city as a whole.  The Order itself is insular and private, revealing little of itself.  Their rituals, variations on the Sacraments as well as a few of their own, would be considered by outsiders as torturous mutilation.%0a> %0a49,59c49,59%0a%3c • ''Comrade'' “Be gay, do crimes,” the experienced Comrades said as the new recruits learned the business.  Comrades of this level gain a free specialty in Larceny, Brawl, or Weaponry.%0a%3c %0a%3c •• ''Comrade'' Comrades know how to do things outside of the purview of Big Brother.  They receive Anonymity • for free.%0a%3c %0a%3c ••• ''Comrade'' The Infoshop is, above all else, a source of information and learning about how the world works.  These Comrades receive a free dot in Politics.%0a%3c %0a%3c •••• ''Comrade'' Anybody who has been a Comrade long enough to reach this level of membership has made a lot of friends in weird places.  Receive Allies ••• distributed as you wish with other supernatural factions in the city.%0a%3c %0a%3c ••••• ''Comrade'' These Comrades have learned some trick they shouldn’t know.  Receive one supernatural ability (no higher than level 1 if levelled).  That ability uses your MCI merit as your supernatural attribute dice pool and any power pool costs are replaced with Willpower costs.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!%25center%25'''The Order of Saint Cervantes de Valladolid'''%0a---%0a> • ''Portero'' The Order knows a hunt will fail if they do not know what they are hunting.  All Portero therefore earn a free specialty in Occult.%0a> %0a> •• ''Alcaide'' The faith of the Alcaide is strong.  By reaching this rank, they have gained Object Fetishism • with their crucifix. %0a> %0a> ••• ''Nuncio'' A Nuncio is a knowledgeable resource to the Order.  They gain a free dot in Academics or Occult at this level.%0a> %0a> •••• ''Comisarios'' By this point the Comisarios has proven themselves worthy of accessing the Order’s Library •••, which includes texts on Academics, Occult, and Investigation.%0a> %0a> ••••• ''Alguacil'' Alguacil must have learned the divine sorceries needed to fight their enemies, including Countermagic •••.%0a> %0a> !!%25center%25'''The Seventh'''%0a63,64c63,64%0a%3c A secretive Catholic Order dedicated to contain and purge supernatural threats to their community.  The group also welcomes practitioners of Santeria and other Catholic-syncretic faiths.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> An organization of “retired” Lost Boys who work together to protect the Executive Circle and the city at large from supernatural threats.  Their ranks have swelled with membership from Cuban and Venezuelan refugees that have come to Miami in the intervening years.%0a> %0a66,67c66,67%0a%3c The Order’s base in Miami, the Church of the Holy Mother, houses a reliquary common to all of the Order’s churches.  The reliquary, a simple hawthorn box tied with old leather, supposedly contains the ring finger of Saint Cervantes de Valladolid himself.  It is the Order’s faith in the Saint and his cause that propels them forward in their purpose.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> A wooden ship’s wheel hangs in the main gathering room at the USCG Seventh District base.  The wheel is the only thing that was recovered from the CGC Tarpon after it was lost at sea during an incursion fighting Those Below.  The wheel, which simply floated to the base and was recovered a week later, is now a constant reminder of the dangers The Seventh face in defending Miami.%0a> %0a69,70c69,70%0a%3c Within the Order, the number one goal is to understand and eliminate threats to the Catholic community they are a part of.  In Miami and their resulting membership in the Executive Circle, they have expanded their mission to the city as a whole.  The Order itself is insular and private, revealing little of itself.  Their rituals, variations on the Sacraments as well as a few of their own, would be considered by outsiders as torturous mutilation.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Seventh operates most of the time as a support organization for its membership, something akin to a VFW chapter that has to facilitate its members' drug addiction.  However, there is a serious military aspect to the group.  The Seventh's leadership is always tracking Those Below, and orders come down to deal with them and other threats Miami faces.  Members in the Seventh are all considered trusted professionals at this point.  Though the vast majority are Lost Boys, not all are, but all are military veterans.%0a> %0a74,98d73%0a%3c • ''Portero'' The Order knows a hunt will fail if they do not know what they are hunting.  All Portero therefore earn a free specialty in Occult.%0a%3c %0a%3c •• ''Alcaide'' The faith of the Alcaide is strong.  By reaching this rank, they have gained Object Fetishism • with their crucifix. %0a%3c %0a%3c ••• ''Nuncio'' A Nuncio is a knowledgeable resource to the Order.  They gain a free dot in Academics or Occult at this level.%0a%3c %0a%3c •••• ''Comisarios'' By this point the Comisarios has proven themselves worthy of accessing the Order’s Library •••, which includes texts on Academics, Occult, and Investigation.%0a%3c %0a%3c ••••• ''Alguacil'' Alguacil must have learned the divine sorceries needed to fight their enemies, including Countermagic •••.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!%25center%25'''The Seventh'''%0a%3c %25center%25(''Mortals/+ only'')%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Purpose''%0a%3c An organization of “retired” Lost Boys who work together to protect the Executive Circle and the city at large from supernatural threats.  Their ranks have swelled with membership from Cuban and Venezuelan refugees that have come to Miami in the intervening years.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Relic''%0a%3c A wooden ship’s wheel hangs in the main gathering room at the USCG Seventh District base.  The wheel is the only thing that was recovered from the CGC Tarpon after it was lost at sea during an incursion fighting Those Below.  The wheel, which simply floated to the base and was recovered a week later, is now a constant reminder of the dangers The Seventh face in defending Miami.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Doctrine''%0a%3c The Seventh operates most of the time as a support organization for its membership, something akin to a VFW chapter that has to facilitate its members' drug addiction.  However, there is a serious military aspect to the group.  The Seventh's leadership is always tracking Those Below, and orders come down to deal with them and other threats Miami faces.  Members in the Seventh are all considered trusted professionals at this point.  Though the vast majority are Lost Boys, not all are, but all are military veterans.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Mechanics''%0a%3c :%25center%25Membership levels:%0a%3c %0a107a83%0a> %0a
